article.headline: N. Dakota St. 83, Oral Roberts 75
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Ben Woodside scored 24 points to help North Dakota State beat Oral Roberts 83-75 Thursday in a matchup of Summit League favorites. Brent Winkelman added 20 points for the Bison (2-3, 1-0 Summit), all but two in the second half. Dominique Morrison scored 19 points and Robert Jarvis 18 for the Golden Eagles (1-5, 0-1), who led 30-28 at half. Oral Roberts was picked in a preseason poll of coaches, media members and sports information directors to defend its regular season conference title. The Bison were picked to finish second.
